    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01298.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">White Hall, Ky.</name>
                    <date when="1891-01-06">Jan. 6. 1891<ptr target="loc.01298_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
            </opener>
                      
            <p>I have just received your "Leaves of Grass &#38;c." 1890&#8212;for which accept my thanks.</p>
            
            <p>I have not found time but to glance over it &#38; cannot return a criticism&#8212;even if such a thing was a consequence.</p>
            
            <p>I am very independent in such matters&#8212;and think with Burns</p>
            
            <p>"Crooning to a body's sel</p>
            <p>Does well enough"<ptr target="loc.01298_n2"/></p>
            
            <p>&#38; let the world read or not, as it likes.</p>
            
                        <closer>
                <salute>&#8212;Wishing you long years yet of health and happiness I remain yours truly</salute>
            <signed>Cassius Marcellus Clay</signed></closer>
            
